  "prompt": "What is \u201ccapital\u201d?",
  "response": "Capital is a broad economic term that can refer to several related concepts:\n\n1. Financial Capital\n- Money used to fund business activities\n- Investments or financial assets\n- Funds used to generate income or start/expand a business\n\n2. Economic Capital\n- Resources used in the production of goods and services\n- Includes physical assets like machinery, equipment, buildings\n- Represents the means of production\n\n3. Human Capital\n- Skills, knowledge, and experience possessed by individuals\n- Contributes to economic productivity and potential earnings\n- Developed through education, training, and personal development\n\n4. Working Capital\n- The difference between a company's current assets and current liabilities\n- Measures a company's short-term financial health and operational efficiency\n\n5. Social Capital\n- Networks of relationships among people that enable social cooperation\n- Includes trust, shared norms, and mutual understanding within a community\n\n6. Intellectual Capital\n- Intangible assets like patents, trademarks, and organizational knowledge\n- Represents accumulated knowledge and intellectual property of an organization\n\nThe specific meaning of \"capital\" depends on the context in which it is used, but generally refers to resources that can be used to generate economic value.",
